
   The REDESCRIBE command is used to redefine an object's description.
   The  object  description  provided  by  the  system is the standard
   object type, e.g., standard file.  You  can  replace  the  standard
   description with a description of your own.

     1.  To REDESCRIBE an object use one of the following options.  If
         an  object  name  is  not  specified  the  current  object is
         assumed.

            - Command Menu - Select REDESCRIBE + RETURN

            - Typed Command - Type redescribe [object_name] + RETURN

     2.  The following message appears:

           Enter the new description:

         Type in the new description for the object.
